<br/><a href="/db/item.html?item=14483;page=1;howmany=50#113095456018117"><img alt="" title="Use this to create a link to this post" src="/shared/garrowrt.png" border="0" height="9" width="11" /> Link to this post</a>
<br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td>
<td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Blue diamonds have dropped in price many sell for 300-350 buy the stack because with the increased use in all hight level smithing and tailoring, they increased the drop rate in many mid-high level zones.  my mid 50's druid was quad kiting in Dulaks harbor and averaged 10-12 a night off the ships, and if I sold all the fire opal/emeralds and star rubies that drop there too, I could get about a stack more. <br />so if your mid/high level you can average about 30 blue diamonds in a 6 hour period.  Not to mention about 1 1/2 levels in that time in the low 50's solo.</p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Enchanter Palladia Mors Master at Bake,Beg,Brew,Fish,Fletch,Jewelcraft,Pottery,Smithing,Tailoring.</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td></tr></table></td></tr></table>
